{"cursor":"2666","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Raymond de Gaufredi' (died 1310) was a Friar Minor from Provence. A sympathizer\nwith the Franciscan Spirituals, he became Minister General of the Order of\nFriars Minor in 1289. On the death of Pope Nicholas IV in 1292, he felt able to\nrelax the sanctions against the Spirituals. He was responsible in particular for\nthe release from prison of Roger Bacon. [http://www.historynet.com/explorat-\nion/science_engineering/3037671.html?page=5&c=y TheHistoryNet | Science &\nEngineering | Roger Bacon ] Angelo da Clareno\nand some of his followers were exiled to Armenia. He nominated Pierre Jean Olivi\nfor a teaching position at the University of Montpellier. [http://66.102.9.-\n104/search?q=cache:RnmRCb3UJPsJ:www.franciscans.org.au/sfo/sfo13/Olivi%2520Four-\n%2520Questions/Introduction.doc+Olivi+Montpellier+Gaufredi&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=14&-\ngl=uk]: \"... promotion by the Minister General, Friar Matthew of Acquasparta,\nand Friar Raymond Gaufredi to the position of Lector of Theology, first (1287)\nin the general School of S. Croce in Florence and then (1289) in that of\nMontpellier.\"\n\nGaufredi was also a supporter of the Franciscan tertiary RamÃ³n Llull. [http://www-\nmat.upc.es/grup_de_grafs/logo/llull_bio.htm], [http://www.ralph-\nabraham.org/ficino/chronos/lull.txt]. He was deposed as Minister General\nby Pope Boniface VIII, in\n1295. [http://www.ewtn.com/PadrePio/franciscan/ofm.htm]: \"Raimondo even\nventured to revise the general constitutions at the General Chapter of Paris in\n1292, whereupon, having refused the Bishopric of Padua offered him by Boniface\nVIII, he was compelled by the pope to resign his office.\"\n\nSome alchemical writings have been attributed to him.\n","linknr":118,"url":"Raimund_Godefroy","recorded":1375077746,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Raymond_de_Gaufredi&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Raymond_de_Gaufredi&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opens